	     Cape Town – A woman was killed and nine people were injured when a bakkie and a car collided on Michell’s Pass, between Worcester and Ceres, on Tuesday, paramedics said. One man was found trapped in the bakkie while a man and woman were trapped in the car, ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said in a statement. All three were in a critical condition. Another three people sustained serious injuries, and four minor to moderate injuries. All the patients were taken to Ceres Provincial Hospital. The critically injured woman died on arrival. The cause of the accident was not yet known.  24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  